{"parse":{"title":"Austrian Latin America Institute","pageid":22701392,"revid":790198963,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Palais_schlick.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Palais_schlick.jpg/220px-Palais_schlick.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Palais_schlick.jpg/330px-Palais_schlick.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Palais_schlick.jpg/440px-Palais_schlick.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"480\" data-file-height=\"640\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Palais_schlick.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Palais Schlick in Vienna</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Austrian Latin America Institute</b> (<i>\u00d6sterreichisches Lateinamerika-Institut</i>, LAI) is an interdisciplinary orientated organisation, aiming at intensifying dialogue and exchange between <a href=\"/wiki/Austria\" title=\"Austria\">Austria</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Latin_America\" title=\"Latin America\">Latin America</a>. It was founded as an association in 1965 and receives subsidies for its work in development politics as well as scientific and cultural events and projects. About half of the annual budget originates from its own resources, mainly language courses as well as membership fees. In 1994 the institute moved to the historic Palais Schlick in <a href=\"/wiki/Vienna\" title=\"Vienna\">Vienna</a>'s 9th district <a href=\"/wiki/Alsergrund\" title=\"Alsergrund\">Alsergrund</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Interdisciplinary_Master_Degree_Programme_in_Latin-American_Studies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Interdisciplinary Master Degree Programme in Latin-American Studies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Library\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Library</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Language_Courses\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Language Courses</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Information_service\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Information service</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Events</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Austrian_Study-Group_for_Latin-American_Research\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Austrian Study-Group for Latin-American Research</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">9</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Literature\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">10</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Literature</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">11</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Interdisciplinary_Master_Degree_Programme_in_Latin-American_Studies\">Interdisciplinary Master Degree Programme in Latin-American Studies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Interdisciplinary Master Degree Programme in Latin-American Studies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Austrian Latin America Institute coordinates the <i>Interdisciplinary Master Degree Programme in Latin-American Studies</i> (<i>Interdisziplin\u00e4rer Universit\u00e4tslehrgang f\u00fcr H\u00f6here Lateinamerika-Studien</i>) in cooperation with the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Vienna\" title=\"University of Vienna\">University of Vienna</a>. This is the only<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \"university level\" course about Latin America in Austria. The degree is <a href=\"/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\">Master of Arts</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Latin_American_studies\" title=\"Latin American studies\">Latin American studies</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Library\">Library</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Library\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Austrian Latin America Institute has the only <a href=\"/wiki/Library\" title=\"Library\">library</a> and documentation centre in Austria specializing in Latin America. The collection focuses on specialist books and journals on economy, politics, history, culture, society and ecology of the Latin American countries. Furthermore, it has literary works by Latin American authors in Spanish and Portuguese and their translations. The library represents Austria in <a href=\"/wiki/REDIAL\" title=\"REDIAL\">REDIAL</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Language_Courses\">Language Courses</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Language Courses\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Austrian Latin America Institute is Austria's largest <a href=\"/wiki/Language_school\" title=\"Language school\">language school</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_language\" title=\"Spanish language\">Spanish</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Portuguese_language\" title=\"Portuguese language\">Portuguese</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Indigenous_languages_of_the_Americas\" title=\"Indigenous languages of the Americas\">Indigenous languages</a> offering about 300 courses annually.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Information_service\">Information service</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Information service\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Austrian Latin America Institute offers information and advice to all people interested in Latin America and Latin American students in particular.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Events\">Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Events\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The event calendar includes exhibitions, book presentations, concerts, lectures and discussions.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Austrian_Study-Group_for_Latin-American_Research\">Austrian Study-Group for Latin-American Research</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Austrian Study-Group for Latin-American Research\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Austrian Latin America Institute itself is no research institute, but it supports the <i>Austrian Study-Group for Latin-American Research</i> (<i>Arbeitsgemeinschaft \u00d6sterreichische Lateinamerikaforschung</i>). The object of this association is scientific networking, interdisciplinary exchange and cooperation of researchers in Austria. It regards itself as an open forum offering young scientists the opportunity to present and discuss their work. In 2007 the Study-Group had  108 members from Austria, Europe and Latin America. The annual conference is held in <a href=\"/wiki/Strobl\" title=\"Strobl\">Strobl am Wolfgangsee</a>. The Study-Group was founded in 1983 by members of the Austrian Latin America Institute and is partner of CEISAL (<i>Consejo Europeo de Investigaciones Sociales de Am\u00e9rica Latina</i>).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>Atenci\u00f3n: Jahrbuch des \u00d6sterreichischen Lateinamerika-Instituts</i>. Yearbook with scholarly articles in German, Spanish and English</li>\n<li><i>Investigaciones: Forschungen zu Lateinamerika</i>. Publication by the <i>Austrian Study-Group for Latin-American Research</i> in which master thesis and dissertations are made accessible to a wider audience</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Ibero-American_Institute\" title=\"Ibero-American Institute\">Ibero-American Institute</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Klein, p. 27</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Literature\">Literature</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Literature\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Marcus Klein: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20070824024832/http://www.cedla.uva.nl/60_publications/PDF_files_publications/72RevistaEuropea/72_Klein.pdf\">Marcus Klein: \u201cLatin America Studies in Austria: An Overview\u201c</a>, in: <i>Revista Europea de Estudios Latinoamericanos y del Caribe</i> (Ed. by CEDLA, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Amsterdam\" title=\"University of Amsterdam\">University of Amsterdam</a>), 72, April 2002.</li>\n<li>Gerhard Drekonja-Kornat (Ed.): <i>Lateinamerikanistik \u2013 der \u00f6sterreichische Weg.</i> LIT, M\u00fcnster u.&#160;a. 2005, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-8258-8651-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-8258-8651-4\">3-8258-8651-4</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Austrian_Latin_America_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20090204143059/http://www.lai.at/es\">Spanish web site</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lai.at/\">German web site</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1272\nCached time: 20180910100203\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.064 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.076 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 292/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1043/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 402/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 15/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 299/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.005/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 591 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   46.980      1 Template:ISBN\n100.00%   46.980      1 -total\n 29.82%   14.009      1 Template:Catalog_lookup_link\n 11.75%    5.522      1 Template:Error-small\n 10.24%    4.812      3 Template:Yesno-no\n  5.66%    2.659      3 Template:Yesno\n  5.46%    2.564      6 Template:Trim\n  4.21%    1.978      1 Template:Main_other\n  2.88%    1.355      1 Template:Tl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:22701392-0!canonical and timestamp 20180910100203 and revision id 790198963\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"de","url":"